<h1>Military Deployment</h1>
<h2>ACCOUNT CANCELLATION OR SUSPENSION FOR MILITARY PERSONNEL</h2>
<h2>AT&T - ACCOUNT CANCELLATION FOR MILITARY PERSONNEL</h2>
<h3>Eligibility</h3>
<p>
	AT&T will waive all early termination fees for those customers called to active duty and/or 
	re-deployed to a non-AT&T service area.
</p>
<ul class="showBullets">
	<li>
		Minnesota military personnel or the spouses of service members who have been issued 
		orders into active duty, deployment, or a permanent change of duty station may cancel 
		without penalty, regardless of whether or not they are going to an AT&T service area.
		<ul class="showBullets">
			<li>
				This applies to any account in the name of the service member or spouse.
			</li>
			<li>
				All or only specified lines of service can be cancelled without penalty 
				if requested for either the service member or spouse.
			</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
	<li>
		Wisconsin military personnel who signed a service agreement prior to entering active 
		military duty are eligible, regardless of whether they are being transferred or deployed 
		elsewhere.
	</li>
</ul>
<p>
	Customers cancelling for Military reasons have two options under the Servicemembers Civil 
	Relief Act (SCRA):
	<ul class="showBullets">
		<li>Cancel the service with no ETF.</li>
		<li>Cancel the service and have their number held for up to 39 months.
			<li class="showBullets">
				At the end of the 39-month period, the service automatically cancels and no 
				ETF is assessed.
			</li>
			<li>
				They may reinstate at any time within the 39 months. There are no extensions 
				allowed beyond the 39 months.
			</li>
		</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<p>
	If the customer who is requesting cancellation due to being transferred or deployed overseas 
	purchased equipment within the past thirty days, they can return their equipment to the point 
	of sale and cancel under the Buyer's Remorse policy as referenced on Equipment Return, Equipment 
	Exchange, and Equipment Cancel (Buyer's Remorse and No Install) Decision Flow (link not accessible 
	by LD - Exclusive, LD - Non-Exclusive, and National Retail).
</p>
<p>
	Military cancellation is offered only to military personnel who are being transferred or deployed 
	to an area outside of the AT&T footprint. This also includes military that are denied access to 
	their phones while working in the military. Eligible military personnel include:
	<ul class="showBullets">
		<li>Basic training/boot camp</li>
		<li>Base-to-base transfers</li>
		<li>Reserve/National Guard being called to active duty</li>
		<li>Domestic/international active-duty deployment</li>
	</ul>
</p>
<h3>Process</h3>
<p>
	<span style="font-style:italic;">Phone:</span>
	Military personnel can call AT&T Wireless Customer Care at 800-331-0500 to request military
	cancellation.
</p>
<p>
	<span style="font-style:italic;">OR</span>
</p>	
<p>
	<span style="font-style:italic;">In Store:</span>
	Military customers simply bring or send in a copy of the transfer documentation or deployment 
	orders to their local AT&T Retail Store and request military cancellation.
</p>
