<h2>T-MOBILE - ACCOUNT SUSPENSION FOR MILITARY PERSONNEL</h2>
<h3>Eligibility</h3>
<p>
	T-Mobile allows military customers to suspend their wireless account due to deployment.
</p>
<ul class="showBullets">
	<li>Maximum military suspension time is 36 months.</li>
	<li>
		No fees during suspension time, however charges are prorated for the partial month 
		of service before suspension. The prorated bill may arrive after the customer's 
		deployment.
	</li>
	<li>
		The customer keeps their mobile number, rate plan, and any current promotions during 
		suspension.
	</li>
	<li>
		For family plans, any active subscribers are billed the normal monthly recurring 
		charge even if there are suspended subscribers.
	</li>
	<li>
		Customer extends their contract for an amount of time equal to the suspension period.
	</li>
</ul>
<h3>Process</h3>
<p>
	<span style="font-style:italic;">Phone:</span>
	 Customer calls T-Mobile Customer Care at 877-453-1304 to request Military Deployment 
	 Suspension benefit.
</p>
<p>
	<span style="font-style:italic;">OR</span>
</p>	
<p>
	<span style="font-style:italic;">In Store:</span>
	 Military customers simply bring or send in a copy of the transfer documentation or 
	 deployment orders to their local T-Mobile Retail Store and request Military Deployment 
	 Suspension benefit.
</p>
